Utterances.UttText: Gerry Cage is a 55yo female with PMHx of hypertension presenting to the clinic with concerns of recent chest pains.

Phrases.PhraseText: a 55yo female with PMHx of hypertension presenting
to the clinic with concerns of recent chest pains.

Utterances.UttText: Three days ago, when she was leaving grocery story, she was walking to the care when she felt onset of substernal chest pains.
She sat in her car for 5-10 minutes and they subsided.
She has had "twinges" of chest pain for the past 4 months, mainly when she is doing some activity like running down the street to get her cat or going up a flight of stairs.

Phrases.PhraseText: of chest pain for the past 4 months,
going up a flight of stairs.

Utterances.UttText: She is currently on lisinopril and chlorthalidone, and does not check her blood pressure at home.
She gets her BP checked once a month at work and is unaware if it is ever abnormal.
Reports a healthy diet with 3 balanced meals, including meats and veggies.

Phrases.PhraseText: a healthy diet with 3 balanced meals,

Utterances.UttText: Social history significant for smoking cigarettes 1ppd x 30 years.

Phrases.PhraseText: significant for smoking cigarettes 1ppd x 30 years.

Utterances.UttText: Family hx:  Mom: HTN, T2DM, Pulmonary aneurysm at 60 yo Dad: Heart Attack at 40 yo Two brothers: Healthy   Objective VS:  BP: 150/92 P: 85 RR: 14 T: 98F  PE:  General: NAD, well-appearing  Lungs: CTAB, normal lungs sounds, no w/c/r Heart: RRR, no m/g/r Abd: Soft, non-tender, non-distended MSK: No LE edema, cyanosis, no tenderness to palpation on ribcage   Assessment:  Ms.

Phrases.PhraseText: Heart Attack at 40 yo Two brothers

Utterances.UttText: Gerry Cage is a 55yo female with PMHx of hypertension and 30 year pack history. presenting to the clinic with concerns of recent chest pains after exertional activity.

Utterances.UttText: Other ddx:  Unstable angina  MI GERD Myocarditis  Plan - Lipid panel, HbgA1c, and BMP to assess for hyperlipidemia and diabetes due to patient risk factors, including family history - Order EKG  - Initiate beta blocker therapy to better control HTN + stable angina - Initiate Aspirin 81mg daily  - Counsel cessation of smoking  - F/u in 4-6 months, sooner if symptoms return
